    "created_at": "2012-08-07T05:30:10Z",
    "updated_at": "2012-08-07T05:30:10Z",
    "body": "I think ARCs call into the runtime to do atomic operations. Now that we have atomic intrinsics, we can use those instead.\n\nI suspect some of the nasty organization in pipes might have been working around compiler bugs, like #3005. The workarounds may not actually be effective though, it could have just been stuff I tried when looking for a workaround that I never removed.\n",
